have received the punishment
they deserve.

56
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,490
Maybe this will give you some comfort.

57
00:03:19,030 --> 00:03:19,870
Can you

58
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:22,400
believe him now?

59
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:26,760
No.

60
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,200
You don't dare to believe?

61
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,200
You don't understand.

62
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,640
Actually,

63
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,450
you really liked him, didn't you?

64
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,320
That's why when you were betrayed,

65
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,600
you were so angry.

66
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,290
I have something to give you.

67
00:03:54,780 --> 00:03:57,340
(Property Deed)

68
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,170
The property deed of my house?

69
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,680
I found it in my dad's study room.

70
00:04:02,670 --> 00:04:03,850
I checked his bank transactions.

71
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:04,990
Five years ago,

72
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,200
my dad withdrew

73
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,090
60 silver dollars.

74
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:08,550
And that day,

75
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,170
your house was sold.

76
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,000
But the broker

77
00:04:15,670 --> 00:04:17,530
didn't mention who bought the house.

78
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:18,880
That was a haunted house.

79
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:20,650
Four people died there in one day.

80
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:21,880
Except for my dad,

81
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,680
who would be foolish enough to buy it?

82
00:04:25,150 --> 00:04:26,830
If I had those 60 silver dollars,

83
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,000
I could live more comfortably

84
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,320
in the United Kingdom.

85
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:33,980
(Property Deed)

86
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,480
What is this?

87
00:04:44,230 --> 00:04:45,960
This is written by the buyer.

88
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:47,050
Who knows what it is?

89
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:52,440
Though I've learned all the laws,

90
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:54,680
I still feel it's like a dream and an illusion.

91
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,530
Why did he...

92
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:00,170
You should ask him about that

93
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,040
if

94
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,760
you can meet him again.

95
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,400
Miss Jiangyun.

96
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,850
Hatred cannot punish others.

97
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:13,290
It only brings pain and destruction.

98
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:15,320
Live for yourself.

99
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,480
The former prisoner held in this cell

100
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,360
was Lawyer Qin.

101
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,800
I asked Captain Chen

102
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:26,360
to lock you in this prison cell.

103
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:28,530
Because I thought

104
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,240
maybe in this way,

105
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,490
you could be closer to each other.

106
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:06,860
(Though I've learned...)

107
00:06:08,150 --> 00:06:09,560
Where should one dwell?

108
00:06:10,590 --> 00:06:12,440
How should one subdue the mind?

109
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,880
Though I've learned all the laws,

110
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,290
I still feel it's like a dream and an illusion.

111
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:49,320
So, what are your plans next?

112
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:50,650
Well, about that,

113
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,760
I should ask you instead.

114
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,850
The court sentenced me

115
00:06:58,830 --> 00:06:59,800
to do volunteer work

116
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,410
here for a year.

117
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:02,760
Three hours a day.

118
00:07:04,150 --> 00:07:05,210
Actually, it's good.

119
00:07:06,470 --> 00:07:07,760
I can help the prisoners here.

120
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:09,320
It's better than staying idle

121
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,440
at home.

122
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:12,160
Are you really planning

123
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,050
to quit lawyering?

124
00:07:14,230 --> 00:07:15,070
No.

125
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,730
But I can't do it in Jiangzhou.

126
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:20,510
By the way,

127
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:21,920
you haven't answered my question yet.

128
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,360
My plan?

129
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,650
I want to stay here with you.

130
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:30,730
With me?

131
00:07:35,670 --> 00:07:37,050
Don't I know you well enough?

132
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:39,440
Ever since you solved

133
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:40,870
that bomb case,

134
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:42,190
your mind

135
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:43,830
has been entirely
on the detective squad.

136
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:44,670
Isn't that right?

137
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:48,490
A father knows his son best.

138
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:52,510
Well then,

139
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:53,920
I won't interfere

140
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:55,510
with your investigations,

141
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,210
but don't cause any trouble,

142
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,450
and make sure to stay safe.

143
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,030
Got it, Dad.

144
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:04,190
Thank you for your understanding.

145
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,150
Alright, go back now.

146
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:08,470
Stop lingering around here.

147
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:09,870
Okay.

148
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,320
Bye, Dad.

149
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,330
How is Lawyer Qin doing?

150
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,090
He's doing great, full of energy.

151
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:27,910
Next,

152
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:29,640
we should go find Song He.

153
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:31,510
Why do we need to find him?

154
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:33,990
Are you planning to...

155
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:35,110
Yes,

156
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,080
I can't wait.

157
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:45,060
(Walking for the Innocent)

158
00:08:45,070 --> 00:08:47,280
Captain, this plaque is a gift
from the people of Jiangzhou.

159
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,590
Captain, you said you would
keep this plaque

160
00:08:53,590 --> 00:08:54,680
for your future son.

161
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:55,520
Shut up.

162
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:57,990
I'm a man

163
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,440
of my word.

164
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:04,910
Captain Song,

165
00:09:05,190 --> 00:09:06,610
if you can't bear to chop it,
just say so.

166
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:08,430
You've been hesitating for so long.

167
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:09,790
Are you going to chop it or not?

168
00:09:09,790 --> 00:09:11,240
If not, we're leaving.

169
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,450
Our butts are sore from sitting.

170
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:13,750
You...

171
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:14,990
Alright, alright.

172
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,570
Mr. Qin is just joking with you.

173
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,200
Have you had enough fun?

174
00:09:22,950 --> 00:09:23,790
Forget it.

175
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,490
The people worked so hard on this,

176
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:27,950
and the calligraphy is so elegant.

177
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,690
It would be a pity to chop it.

178
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:32,390
How about this?

179
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:33,880
You two take it back

180
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,110
and hang it in my office.

181
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,560
What did he say?

182
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:40,690
His office?

183
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:46,260
(Walking for the Innocent)

184
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:53,400
Mao Shuai, lift your side a bit higher.

185
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,600
Okay.

186
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,840
Detective Qin,

187
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,730
your coffee is the best.

188
00:09:59,150 --> 00:10:00,040
Oh my,

189
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,520
I really love it

190
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,640
when you call me Detective Qin.

191
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,120
Xiaofan, say it a few more times.

192
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:06,930
Detective Qin.

193
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,440
Detective Qin.

194
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:09,960
Stop it!

195
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,680
Can someone explain it to me?

196
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:13,760
What's going on here?

197
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,600
Why did Director Xu give special approval

198
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,930
for Qin Huole to join our police station

199
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:18,450
and even set up

200
00:10:18,450 --> 00:10:20,120
a separate
psychological analysis department?

201
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:20,960
And he doesn't report to me.

202
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:24,030
Through psychological analysis,

203
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:25,070
Mr. Qin solved the bomb case

204
00:10:25,070 --> 00:10:25,970
and the human clock case.

205
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:27,760
Now everyone in the office

206
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,850
is very interested
in his case-solving methods.

207
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:30,930
I think it's great.

208
00:10:31,270 --> 00:10:32,240
Our station

209
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,790
should embrace such new technologies,

210
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:34,630
shouldn't we?

211
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:40,030
Tell me,

212
00:10:40,430 --> 00:10:41,460
what kind of tricks did you use?

213
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:46,360
Didn't Commander Lei say
he wanted to repay me?

214
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:47,850
I didn't accept it,

215
00:10:48,270 --> 00:10:49,110
but

216
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:50,250
I asked him for another favor.

217
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:55,190
(Special approval for Qin Huole
to join the police station.)

218
00:10:55,190 --> 00:10:56,030
Join the police station.

219
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:07,240
Who told you to put this here?

220
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,680
Move it over.

221
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,090
Are you not listening to me anymore?

222
00:11:11,310 --> 00:11:12,150
This is an order!

223
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,560
Yes, sir.

224
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:16,110
Wait.

225
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,250
Are you trying to get away with it like this?

226
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,360
I don't agree.

227
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,040
It's easy to handle this.

228
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,760
Put it in my place first.

229
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:33,360
I'll keep it for you.

230
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,550
A year from today,

231
00:11:34,550 --> 00:11:35,600
